ORLANDO Pirates have sent trio Mthokozisi Dube, Gladwin Shitolo and Justice Chabalala out on loan ahead of the 2020-21 season. The Buccaneers have made a number of signing including the likes of Thulani Hlatshwayo, Wayde Jooste, Terrence Dzvukamanja and Deon Hotto and now need to make space in their squad. As a result, some players have had to make way for the new arrivals. Dube, Shitolo and Chabalala have found themselves being surplus to requirements at Bucs this season. Golden Arrows will be Dube and Shitolo's home this season while Chabalala returns to Bloemfontein Celtic where he was on loan last season. "Orlando Pirates Football Club has agreed for Mthokozisi Dube and Gladwin Shitolo to join Golden Arrows on loan," the club wrote on their officiual website."The duo will be at Abafana Bes’thende for the 2020/21 season."The club can also confirm that the club has agreed to extend Justice Chabalala’s stay at Bloemfontein Celtic for another season." 